      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "hERG blockers commonly show:\n- **A basic, protonatable N** that can form electrostatic interactions in the pore region.\n- **Hydrophobic/aromatic groups** that engage in \u03c0/van der Waals interactions with aromatic residues lining the channel cavity (classically Tyr/Phe residues).\n- **A geometry/length** that positions the cation and aromatics to fit the inner vestibule.",
