    {
      "step_id": "17a9b27d",
      "step_index": 6,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**In this molecule:**\n- The **piperidine N** is likely **protonated**, providing the key **cationic anchor**.\n- The **benzyl substituent** and the **amide-linked fused aromatic system** provide **two hydrophobic \u201cwings\u201d** around the basic center\u2014this is strongly associated with hERG affinity.\n- The **amide** adds polarity and conformational preference, but it **does not eliminate** the core cationic + hydrophobic pharmacophore; many potent hERG blockers contain amides.\n- The **aryl ketone** and **additional carbonyls** may slightly reduce overall lipophilicity and can increase PSA, which sometimes lowers hERG risk\u2014but here the molecule still has substantial aromatic surface area and a strong basic center.",
